replies.bodyText:
I don't see a case where an empty expression would be valid. I can imagine cases where maybe a value is optional and so an empty expression is benign.
My overall instinct is not to make any assumptions here. I think the validators are the perfect place to assess whether an empty expression can be valid. This place here could be called from anywhere.
Speaking of validators, right now the ZeebeExpressionValidator will accept null and empty values:
  private void validateExpression(
      final String expression, final ValidationResultCollector resultCollector) {

    if (expression == null || expression.isEmpty()) {
      return;
    }

If you say, this should always be considered an invalid user input, we could change that.
I also wonder whether long term we could have a connection between ZeebeTaskDefinitionImpl#registerType and ZeebeRuntimeValidators. I.e. maybe the runtime validators could be derived from the model constraints.
Like I noticed in the retries issue that when I pass an empty expression, it falls back to the default value. So those two things seem somewhat related to me.

